The '''black-throated shrikebill''' or '''black-faced shrikebill''' ('''''Clytorhynchus nigrogularis''''') is a [[songbird]] [[species]] in the [[Family (taxonomy)|family]] [[Monarchidae]].

It is found in [[Fiji]] and [[Solomon Islands]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

The black-throated shrikebill was originally described in the genus ''[[Triller|Lalage]]''. The [[Santa Cruz shrikebill]] was split from the black-throated shrikebill in 2008 but some authorities still consider it to be its [[subspecies]], ''C. n. sanctaecrucis''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldbirdnames.org/updates/archives/species-v1/|title=Species Version 1 « IOC World Bird List|website=worldbirdnames.org|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref>

